body:
Related to #6062 and #3149

**Describe the bug**
DayTimeIntervalType inside Structs are not a supported type. Found when adding new tests for struct binary ops in `cmp_test.py`. Adding intervals in structs via `StructGen([['child0', StructGen([['child2', DayTimeIntervalGen()]])], ['child1', short_gen]])` causes a test failure due to `part of the plan is not columnar`.

```
      !Expression <Literal> [[6084712057446794809],32767] cannot run on GPU because expression Literal [[6084712057446794809],32767] produces an unsupported type StructType(StructField(child0,StructType(StructField(child2,DayTimeIntervalType(0,3),true)),true),StructField(child1,ShortType,true))
```

Reproduction:
Add `# @pytest.mark.parametrize('data_gen', [DayTimeIntervalGen(), StructGen([['child0', StructGen([['child2', DayTimeIntervalGen()]])], ['child1', short_gen]])], ids=idfn)` to any interval test and execute.

